<section xmlns="http://xml.house.gov/schemas/uslm/1.0" style="-uslm-lc:I80" id="id789bbd3e-6992-11f1-ab3f-8b4c043f8cd5" identifier="/us/usc/t16/s777i"><num value="777i">§ 777i.</num><heading> Rules and regulations</heading><content>
<p style="-uslm-lc:I11" class="indent0">The Secretary of the Interior is authorized to make rules and regulations for carrying out the provisions of this chapter.</p>
</content><sourceCredit id="id789bbd3f-6992-11f1-ab3f-8b4c043f8cd5">(<ref href="/us/act/1950-08-09/ch658/s10">Aug. 9, 1950, ch. 658, § 10</ref>, <ref href="/us/stat/64/434">64 Stat. 434</ref>.)</sourceCredit>
<notes type="uscNote" id="id789bbd40-6992-11f1-ab3f-8b4c043f8cd5">
<note style="-uslm-lc:I74" role="crossHeading" topic="execDoc" id="id789bbd41-6992-11f1-ab3f-8b4c043f8cd5"><heading class="centered"><b>Executive Documents</b></heading></note>
<note style="-uslm-lc:I85" topic="transferOfFunctions" id="id789bbd42-6992-11f1-ab3f-8b4c043f8cd5">
<heading class="centered smallCaps">Transfer of Functions</heading>
<p style="-uslm-lc:I21" class="indent0">Transfer of functions to Secretary of Commerce from Secretary of the Interior by Reorg. Plan No. 4 of 1970, eff. <date date="1970-10-03">Oct. 3, 1970</date>, 35 F.R. 15627, <ref href="/us/stat/84/2090">84 Stat. 2090</ref>, see note set out under <ref href="/us/usc/t16/s777">section 777 of this title</ref>.</p>
</note>
